# Environment variables

When a feature needs new configuration:

1. Add the variable to **`.env.example`** with a placeholder and a one-line comment.
2. Add the same key to **`.env.local`** (preserve existing values; use empty string or placeholder if the user must fill it in).
3. Add TypeScript types in **`src/vite-env.d.ts`** for any `VITE_*` client vars.
4. Read server vars via **`server/lib/config.ts`** helpers when possible (don't scatter `process.env` checks).

Never commit real secrets to `.env.example`. Never overwrite existing secret values in `.env.local` when adding new keys.

Current required keys:

| Key | Where | Purpose |
|-----|-------|---------|
| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | server | Hosted AI |
| `APP_URL` | server | OAuth redirects |
| `CMO_API_TOKEN` / `VITE_CMO_API_TOKEN` | server + client | Local dev API auth |
| `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` / `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | client | Cloud sign-in |
| `SUPABASE_URL` / `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | server | Workspace DB |
| `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` / `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` | server | GSC + GA4 OAuth |
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` / `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` | server | Billing webhooks |
| `STRIPE_PRICE_PRO_MONTHLY` / `STRIPE_PRICE_TEAM_MONTHLY` | server | Checkout price IDs |
